WEBVTT

00:07.441 --> 00:08.075
‐ Previously,
on "The Purge"...

00:09.476 --> 00:10.744
‐ Be careful.

00:10.777 --> 00:12.346
When we bottle up our feelings,
they can come out

00:12.379 --> 00:14.414
in other ways
that might be scary.

00:14.448 --> 00:17.251
‐ Hey.
‐ [gasping]

00:17.284 --> 00:19.186
‐ I'm sorry.
‐ [whimpering]

00:19.219 --> 00:21.154
‐ There's the coward I know.

00:21.188 --> 00:23.423
‐ So you think
you can take down the NFFA?

00:23.457 --> 00:25.325
‐ They're killing
innocent people off‐Purge

00:25.359 --> 00:26.593
and I think I found the proof.

00:26.627 --> 00:29.263
‐ About Esme:
whatever she was up to,

00:29.296 --> 00:31.465
chances are she'll make some
sort of move on Purge Night.

00:31.498 --> 00:33.367
‐ I'm in.

00:33.400 --> 00:34.635
‐ The system reboot has
everyone distracted for a bit,

00:34.668 --> 00:36.270
but you have to move fast.

00:36.303 --> 00:37.337
‐ [screams]
‐ Get in the back!

00:37.371 --> 00:39.606
‐ Glen, let's finish this
man to man.

00:39.640 --> 00:41.074
‐ Michelle, Michelle!
[gasping]

00:41.108 --> 00:42.342
‐ Look, there's nothing else
I can do for her

00:42.376 --> 00:45.012
and the hospitals are closed!

00:45.045 --> 00:47.014
‐ I know where to take her:
the triage centers.

00:47.047 --> 00:49.082
‐ [panting]

00:49.116 --> 00:51.318
‐ Oh, shit!

00:51.351 --> 00:52.786
‐ Come on, he's still alive.

00:52.819 --> 00:54.321
[dramatic music]

00:54.354 --> 00:56.156
‐ Officers, move them forward!

00:56.189 --> 00:58.058
‐ I got a friend
who's gonna get us out of here.

00:58.091 --> 01:00.227
‐ Shit, go, go, go!
[overlapping chatter]

01:00.260 --> 01:02.129
‐ Go, go, go!
‐ So what's the plan?

01:02.162 --> 01:03.263
Drive around all night
until Purge is over?

01:03.297 --> 01:05.365
‐ Not without our money.
‐ And where is that?

01:05.399 --> 01:06.233
‐ The Jackals have it.

01:06.266 --> 01:07.501
‐ Ryan tipped them off

01:07.534 --> 01:09.336
so they would
steal the money from Ziv

01:09.369 --> 01:11.204
while we got you
out of prison.

01:11.238 --> 01:12.639
‐ Sounds like the Jackals
were right on time.

01:12.673 --> 01:14.975
‐ Let's go get our money.

01:17.177 --> 01:19.713
‐ We have installed speakers
throughout the city

01:19.746 --> 01:21.181
every, uh, 3.7 blocks

01:21.214 --> 01:24.651
as the NFFA has recommended.

01:24.685 --> 01:27.487
New Orleans is ready
for the Purge, sir.

01:27.521 --> 01:29.089
‐ Have you tested the sirens?

01:29.122 --> 01:31.258
‐ Uh, yes, sir.
[laughs nervously]

01:31.291 --> 01:33.560
Think we, uh, freaked out
a couple neighborhood kids

01:33.594 --> 01:35.696
and scared their parents
a little bit.

01:35.729 --> 01:36.897
‐ They'll get used to it.

01:36.930 --> 01:38.465
‐ Sir, a lot of folks
seem to think

01:38.498 --> 01:40.100
that this is just a stunt.

01:40.133 --> 01:42.603
They‐‐they don't believe
that regular people

01:42.636 --> 01:45.238
will actually go out
and commit crimes.

01:45.272 --> 01:47.207
‐ Our research indicates

01:47.240 --> 01:49.409
that participation
will be very high.

01:49.443 --> 01:51.511
[tense music]

01:51.545 --> 01:53.547
‐ Great, that is‐‐

01:53.580 --> 01:56.583
that is so great.

01:56.617 --> 01:59.086
Anyway, we, uh, have
verified the Wi‐Fi

01:59.119 --> 02:01.054
and, uh, cell phone signals,

02:01.088 --> 02:02.022
installed 2‐inch‐thick

02:02.055 --> 02:04.524
laminate, uh,
bulletproof glass,

02:04.558 --> 02:07.427
and, uh, even upgraded
the security door.

02:07.461 --> 02:10.364
End‐to‐end
rotating keycard encryption.

02:10.397 --> 02:13.533
Only the operators
and managers can get inside.

02:13.567 --> 02:14.468
Um...

02:14.501 --> 02:15.535
[panel buzzes, beeps]

02:15.569 --> 02:17.404
And, uh...

02:17.437 --> 02:19.206
[panel buzzing, beeping]

02:19.239 --> 02:21.708
[stammers]
Hang on a second.

02:21.742 --> 02:23.543
Sometimes it's a little‐‐

02:23.577 --> 02:25.846
‐ So you don't have access

02:25.879 --> 02:27.748
in or out of this room.

02:27.781 --> 02:29.316
Have I got this right?

02:29.349 --> 02:30.450
‐ I think it's probably
just a glitch‐‐

02:30.484 --> 02:32.619
‐ Because this room is
our only way of communicating

02:32.653 --> 02:34.287
with the public on Purge Night.

02:34.321 --> 02:36.223
‐ Yes, I know that,

02:36.256 --> 02:37.724
and I take that
very seriously, sir.

02:37.758 --> 02:38.859
‐ Do you?

02:38.892 --> 02:41.628
Because if you can't
do your job,

02:41.662 --> 02:45.365
the NFFA will take measures
to replace you.

02:45.399 --> 02:47.367
♪ ♪

02:47.401 --> 02:49.736
‐ Uh, no need
to take measures, sir.

02:49.770 --> 02:52.439
I am, uh, gonna
make a phone call.

02:52.472 --> 02:55.742
I'll get right on top of it.

02:55.776 --> 02:57.411
[line beeps]

02:57.444 --> 03:00.414
[line trilling]

03:00.447 --> 03:05.185
♪ ♪

03:05.218 --> 03:06.253
‐ Hello?
‐ James.

03:06.286 --> 03:08.455
[whispering]
Hi, buddy, listen,

03:08.488 --> 03:10.457
having a little issue
with the system you installed.

03:10.490 --> 03:12.859
‐ Well, why don't you tell me
what's going on.

03:12.893 --> 03:13.994
‐ What's going on is that

03:14.027 --> 03:17.164
my regional inspector
is here, okay?

03:17.197 --> 03:19.132
I can't get the damn door open.

03:19.166 --> 03:20.300
‐ Okay, okay.

03:20.333 --> 03:22.436
I want you to know,
most of the time,

03:22.469 --> 03:25.172
this does come down
to operator error.

03:25.205 --> 03:26.840
‐ "Operator."
That's great.

03:26.873 --> 03:28.275
Are you blaming me right now?
‐ No, no, no.

03:28.308 --> 03:31.645
I'm just saying, is it possible
that maybe the last time

03:31.678 --> 03:34.781
you used the door,
you forgot to swipe the card?

03:34.815 --> 03:37.718
Possible?
‐ I don't know, maybe, um...

03:37.751 --> 03:39.653
‐ Yeah, well, there's
your problem, right there.

03:39.686 --> 03:42.556
Just engage and disengage
manually and it'll reset.

03:42.589 --> 03:44.191
Everything will be fine.

03:44.224 --> 03:46.359
‐ Yeah, it better be.
‐ It will.

03:46.393 --> 03:50.497
This is the same system I use
to protect my own family.

03:50.530 --> 03:53.233
You've got nothing
to worry about.

03:53.266 --> 03:56.236
[dramatic music]

03:56.269 --> 04:03.310
♪ ♪

04:08.982 --> 04:11.985
[suspenseful music]

04:12.018 --> 04:19.192
♪ ♪

04:26.233 --> 04:28.301
‐ Jackals already blew through
the meeting point.

04:28.335 --> 04:29.936
Now they're heading west
on Interstate 10.

04:29.970 --> 04:31.171
‐ Just as we expected.

04:31.204 --> 04:32.105
We knew they were
never gonna hold up

04:32.139 --> 04:33.940
their end of the bargain.

04:33.974 --> 04:35.342
I've got a plan
to cut them off.

04:35.375 --> 04:38.245
‐ Good, I won't let
those assholes get the cash.

04:38.278 --> 04:39.846
Not after what they did.

04:39.880 --> 04:41.014
‐ Yeah, they already tried
to kill Doug last year.

04:41.047 --> 04:42.582
‐ Yeah, took that
into an account

04:42.616 --> 04:44.584
when I was doing
my shopping this year.

04:44.618 --> 04:47.320
‐ Multiple reports of an
explosion in the Super Dome.

04:47.354 --> 04:49.856
En route.

04:49.890 --> 04:51.691
[radio chatter]

04:51.725 --> 04:54.561
‐ Any word on Esme?

04:54.594 --> 04:57.597
‐ She should be inside
the command center.

04:57.631 --> 04:59.699
Hopefully, she'll find
the video she's looking for.

04:59.733 --> 05:00.801
[radio chatter]

05:00.834 --> 05:02.536
‐ Who's "Esme"?

05:02.569 --> 05:07.741
♪ ♪

05:07.774 --> 05:09.743
‐ She helped us
with the airport plan.

05:09.776 --> 05:13.413
‐ Yeah, and her and Ryan
kind of had a thing.

05:13.446 --> 05:15.582
‐ Damn, I missed a lot
on the inside.

05:15.615 --> 05:17.717
‐ Heads‐up, we've got
some traffic up ahead.

05:17.751 --> 05:19.586
Looks like two cars
coming in hot.

05:19.619 --> 05:21.721
[dramatic music]

05:21.755 --> 05:23.323
‐ What do I do?
‐ Don't slow down.

05:23.356 --> 05:24.891
Punch it.

05:24.925 --> 05:28.328
♪ ♪

05:28.361 --> 05:30.597
[truck horn honking]

05:30.630 --> 05:31.898
Good job.
We're clear.

05:31.932 --> 05:33.033
Let's find a way
to get off of this.

05:33.066 --> 05:35.402
‐ All right.
Take the next exit.

05:35.435 --> 05:37.337
‐ Bridge on Eleven is out.

05:37.370 --> 05:39.139
It's non‐op.
I repeat: no‐go.

05:39.172 --> 05:41.341
‐ Eleventh's out.

05:41.374 --> 05:42.509
‐ Okay, that means
they're taking the parkway.

05:42.542 --> 05:44.344
Let's roll.

05:44.377 --> 05:51.418
♪ ♪

05:56.022 --> 05:57.524
‐ Marcus...
‐ Hang on, babe.

05:57.557 --> 06:00.126
We're almost there.
Andre, man, come on.

06:00.160 --> 06:02.429
You gotta drive
a little faster.

06:02.462 --> 06:04.831
‐ Help us!
‐ Don't slow down, babe.

06:04.865 --> 06:06.933
There's nothing you can do
for them.

06:06.967 --> 06:08.902
‐ Get us out of here!

06:08.969 --> 06:11.838
‐ Please, please help!

06:11.872 --> 06:13.440
‐ Help!
‐ Help me!

06:13.473 --> 06:16.376
‐ What are you doing?
‐ Help me, please!

06:16.409 --> 06:17.844
Help!
‐ Do something!

06:17.878 --> 06:22.816
♪ ♪

06:22.849 --> 06:25.552
‐ Right up here on the right!

06:25.585 --> 06:27.888
[crowd shouting]

06:27.921 --> 06:31.458
♪ ♪

06:31.491 --> 06:34.327
‐ [groaning]

06:34.361 --> 06:36.630
‐ Hey, hey, hey,
I need some help over here!

06:36.663 --> 06:38.498
My wife, she's been stabbed,

06:38.531 --> 06:40.000
and I got a patient
in the back!

06:40.033 --> 06:42.002
♪ ♪

06:42.035 --> 06:44.504
‐ [groaning]

06:44.537 --> 06:46.740
[indistinct chatter]

06:46.773 --> 06:48.575
‐ What you need?
‐ Give me a gurney.

06:48.608 --> 06:51.478
[suspenseful music]

06:51.511 --> 06:53.980
♪ ♪

06:54.014 --> 06:56.683
‐ We have a class five weapons
activity spike

06:56.716 --> 06:58.151
on sector three.

06:58.184 --> 07:00.487
All personnel, please report

07:00.520 --> 07:02.989
to the surveillance center
immediately.

07:03.023 --> 07:06.092
♪ ♪

07:06.126 --> 07:08.828
We have a class five weapons
activity spike

07:08.862 --> 07:10.196
on sector three.

07:10.230 --> 07:12.499
All personnel, please report

07:12.532 --> 07:14.901
to the surveillance center
immediately.

07:14.935 --> 07:19.039
♪ ♪

07:19.072 --> 07:21.374
‐ Okay...

07:21.408 --> 07:24.177
[keys tapping,
computer chirping]

07:24.210 --> 07:31.418
♪ ♪

07:34.054 --> 07:37.023
[music intensifies]

07:37.057 --> 07:39.993
[suspenseful music]

07:40.026 --> 07:47.067
♪ ♪

07:51.571 --> 07:53.773
‐ Holy shit.

07:53.807 --> 07:56.710
I knew it.
I knew it, I knew it.

07:56.743 --> 07:58.445
Okay.

07:58.478 --> 08:05.518
♪ ♪

08:06.486 --> 08:08.221
[computer beeps]
What?

08:08.254 --> 08:15.428
♪ ♪

08:33.213 --> 08:40.286
♪ ♪

08:46.826 --> 08:48.762
[mouse clicks]

08:48.795 --> 08:51.531
[indistinct chatter]

08:51.564 --> 08:54.100
♪ ♪

08:54.134 --> 08:56.102
‐ Doctor, she's urgent!

08:56.136 --> 08:57.637
‐ She's got a stab wound
right upper chest.

08:57.670 --> 08:58.972
I decompressed her
about ten minutes ago,

08:59.005 --> 09:01.641
but she's gonna
need a chest tube.

09:01.674 --> 09:03.543
‐ You a physician?
‐ An ER doctor.

09:03.576 --> 09:04.844
I trained downtown.

09:04.878 --> 09:06.112
‐ Good, we're low
on doctors tonight.

09:06.146 --> 09:08.114
‐ You guys stocked
in O‐negative?

09:08.148 --> 09:09.516
‐ Yeah, we are.
‐ Okay, I need a set of hands.

09:09.549 --> 09:11.684
‐ Best I can do is
a third year pre‐med student.

09:11.718 --> 09:13.620
‐ I'll take it.
‐ Go.

09:13.653 --> 09:16.156
♪ ♪

09:16.189 --> 09:19.492
‐ [labored breathing]

09:19.526 --> 09:25.031
♪ ♪

09:25.065 --> 09:27.700
‐ Hey, hey.
You're safe here.

09:27.734 --> 09:29.569
♪ ♪

09:29.602 --> 09:31.538
I'm just gonna check
your lungs.

09:31.571 --> 09:33.807
♪ ♪

09:33.840 --> 09:36.576
‐ [labored breathing]

09:36.609 --> 09:40.213
♪ ♪

09:40.246 --> 09:45.285
♪ ♪

09:52.258 --> 09:53.993
‐ Doctor Moore?

09:54.027 --> 09:55.695
I'm here to assist you.

09:55.728 --> 09:58.531
‐ All right, we need to
perform a thoracostomy.

09:58.565 --> 09:59.499
‐ I've never done this before.

09:59.532 --> 10:01.501
I don't know
that I'm qualified.

10:01.534 --> 10:02.635
‐ You haven't even taken
the MCATs

10:02.669 --> 10:04.838
and you're spending
your Purge Night here.

10:04.871 --> 10:07.006
You know what that tells me?
‐ No.

10:07.040 --> 10:09.509
‐ You're gonna be
a great doctor.

10:09.542 --> 10:11.177
‐ Thanks.

10:11.211 --> 10:13.680
♪ ♪

10:13.713 --> 10:15.682
Okay, tell me
what you need me to do.

10:15.715 --> 10:19.018
‐ All right, I need you to get
100 milligrams of ketamine

10:19.052 --> 10:21.287
and a bag of O‐negative.
‐ 'Kay.

10:21.321 --> 10:26.693
♪ ♪

10:26.726 --> 10:29.629
‐ Baby...
Baby, I'm scared.

10:29.662 --> 10:32.031
‐ I got you, okay?

10:32.065 --> 10:33.833
I promise...

10:33.867 --> 10:35.034
♪ ♪

10:35.068 --> 10:37.270
There is no way in hell

10:37.303 --> 10:40.039
that I'm gonna let you die.

10:40.073 --> 10:41.708
‐ I love you.

10:41.741 --> 10:43.209
‐ I love you.

10:43.243 --> 10:50.250
♪ ♪

10:56.256 --> 10:57.824
[door opening]

10:57.857 --> 10:59.726
‐ It's me, it's me.

10:59.759 --> 11:03.062
[breathing heavily]
Did you get to the servers?

11:03.096 --> 11:05.231
‐ The official footage
was deleted.

11:05.265 --> 11:07.233
But that mail truck camera?

11:07.267 --> 11:09.736
It caught them breaking in.

11:09.769 --> 11:12.906
It's proof the NFFA
killed her off‐Purge.

11:12.939 --> 11:16.109
‐ So now The Foundation's
gonna blast it out, right?

11:16.142 --> 11:17.477
‐ Uh, the file was protected.

11:17.510 --> 11:20.246
I couldn't transfer it
outside the closed system.

11:20.280 --> 11:21.981
‐ Don't tell me
this was all for nothing.

11:22.015 --> 11:23.082
‐ Of course not.

11:23.116 --> 11:25.151
I'm gonna make sure
everyone sees this.

11:25.185 --> 11:26.953
‐ How?

11:26.986 --> 11:29.756
‐ I could transfer the file
within the system, so I did.

11:29.789 --> 11:30.757
♪ ♪

11:30.790 --> 11:33.760
[computer chirps]

11:33.793 --> 11:35.995
To the broadcast room.

11:36.029 --> 11:38.097
♪ ♪

11:38.131 --> 11:39.866
‐ You would be
a sitting duck in there.

11:39.899 --> 11:42.802
‐ I know, Vivian.
I know, and I'm gonna do it.

11:42.835 --> 11:46.806
So I just need a manager's
key card to get in.

11:46.839 --> 11:48.808
‐ [sighs]

11:48.841 --> 11:51.811
[suspenseful music]

11:51.844 --> 11:58.818
♪ ♪

12:04.924 --> 12:06.659
‐ Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Stop, stop, stop!

12:06.693 --> 12:08.228
[tires squeal]

12:08.261 --> 12:10.830
‐ Shit!
‐ What the fuck is that?

12:10.863 --> 12:16.836
♪ ♪

12:16.869 --> 12:18.204
It's a trap!
Back up, back up!

12:18.238 --> 12:20.039
Get us out of here!

12:20.073 --> 12:22.675
♪ ♪

12:22.709 --> 12:24.410
[tires squealing]

12:24.444 --> 12:27.347
♪ ♪

12:27.380 --> 12:29.649
[engine rattling]

12:29.682 --> 12:31.317
[dramatic music]

12:31.351 --> 12:32.986
‐ Fuck!

12:33.019 --> 12:34.420
‐ [panting]
‐ [groans]

12:34.454 --> 12:36.155
‐ You okay?
‐ Yeah.

12:36.189 --> 12:38.224
Yeah, we're in position.
‐ 10‐4.

12:38.258 --> 12:40.126
I'm moving into position now.

12:40.159 --> 12:42.695
Tommy, you got our six.

12:42.729 --> 12:49.702
♪ ♪

13:01.381 --> 13:01.748
[suspenseful music]

13:04.150 --> 13:07.420
♪ ♪

13:07.453 --> 13:09.422
‐ [grunting]
‐ Come on, man, let's go!

13:09.455 --> 13:12.558
[engine turning over]

13:12.592 --> 13:14.961
‐ Fuck, fuck!
[panting]

13:14.994 --> 13:16.729
[grunting]

13:16.763 --> 13:18.731
♪ ♪

13:18.765 --> 13:20.466
‐ What's wrong?
‐ It's blocked!

13:20.500 --> 13:22.502
I can't get a shot!

13:22.535 --> 13:24.971
♪ ♪

13:25.004 --> 13:27.106
[steam hissing]

13:27.140 --> 13:30.109
[engine stalling]

13:30.143 --> 13:34.714
♪ ♪

13:34.747 --> 13:38.084
‐ Ready to blast
in 60 seconds.

13:38.117 --> 13:40.987
[sinister music]

13:41.020 --> 13:45.491
♪ ♪

13:45.525 --> 13:46.859
‐ Oh, shit.

13:46.893 --> 13:49.762
What's going on?
Did the Jackals come back?

13:49.796 --> 13:51.764
‐ No way.
Those assholes are long gone.

13:51.798 --> 13:54.100
Did not come all this way
to get fucked up by some rando.

13:54.133 --> 13:58.971
♪ ♪

13:59.005 --> 14:00.940
‐ More Purgers inbound.

14:00.973 --> 14:03.576
♪ ♪

14:03.609 --> 14:07.080
[both grunting]

14:07.113 --> 14:09.148
‐ Doug, your ten!
Behind the crate!

14:09.182 --> 14:12.785
♪ ♪

14:12.819 --> 14:15.822
‐ [hollers]

14:15.855 --> 14:17.623
‐ We're trapped.

14:17.657 --> 14:19.659
‐ You think they're gonna
come back for us?

14:19.692 --> 14:21.627
‐ Would you?

14:21.661 --> 14:23.262
♪ ♪

14:23.296 --> 14:25.598
‐ Alley's clear.
‐ Reloading!

14:25.631 --> 14:27.800
♪ ♪

14:27.834 --> 14:29.635
‐ Sara, up top on your seven!

14:29.669 --> 14:32.605
♪ ♪

14:32.638 --> 14:35.208
[both grunting]

14:35.241 --> 14:41.180
♪ ♪

14:41.214 --> 14:42.982
‐ We're clear.

14:43.015 --> 14:44.517
♪ ♪

14:44.550 --> 14:46.652
‐ [groans, hisses]

14:46.686 --> 14:49.422
I hate Purge Night.
‐ Last one.

14:49.455 --> 14:50.957
‐ All right,
everyone in the van.

14:50.990 --> 14:53.025
Let's blow this thing open.

14:53.059 --> 14:56.662
♪ ♪

14:56.696 --> 14:57.797
‐ Hoo‐hoo‐hoo.

14:57.830 --> 14:59.966
Feel like a kid at Christmas.

14:59.999 --> 15:02.635
‐ Detonation in three, two...

15:02.668 --> 15:09.675
♪ ♪

15:10.910 --> 15:13.713
‐ [laughs]

15:21.287 --> 15:23.656
Holy shit.

15:23.689 --> 15:30.730
♪ ♪

15:32.031 --> 15:34.700
[indistinct chatter]

15:34.734 --> 15:37.703
[phone ringing]

15:37.737 --> 15:39.839
[tense music]

15:39.872 --> 15:42.041
‐ Is there
any other way upstairs?

15:42.074 --> 15:43.976
‐ No.

15:44.010 --> 15:45.812
♪ ♪

15:45.845 --> 15:47.680
[whispers]
Let's go.

15:47.713 --> 15:54.720
♪ ♪

15:55.955 --> 15:58.024
‐ Excuse me.

16:08.968 --> 16:10.970
[drawer clatters]

16:11.003 --> 16:14.774
♪ ♪

16:14.807 --> 16:16.776
‐ [breathing heavily]

16:16.809 --> 16:21.247
♪ ♪

16:21.280 --> 16:22.915
‐ Come on, come on, come on,
come on...

16:26.352 --> 16:27.620
‐ Uh, everyone?
[stammering]

16:27.653 --> 16:29.255
Uh, everybody, I just, um‐‐

16:29.288 --> 16:33.392
I just want to say thank you
for making my first year here‐‐

16:33.426 --> 16:35.228
year here so wonderful,

16:35.261 --> 16:38.931
and, um, let's not
miss anything this year.

16:38.965 --> 16:40.733
Okay?

16:40.766 --> 16:42.735
Yeah, okay.

16:42.768 --> 16:44.637
♪ ♪

16:44.670 --> 16:46.272
You...

16:46.305 --> 16:53.312
♪ ♪

17:00.286 --> 17:02.088
‐ Director Anders?

17:05.825 --> 17:08.794
[monitor beeping]

17:08.828 --> 17:14.934
♪ ♪

17:14.967 --> 17:16.168
[monitor beeping rapidly]

17:16.202 --> 17:17.970
‐ Let me have the clamp.

17:18.004 --> 17:21.707
♪ ♪

17:21.741 --> 17:22.942
Come on.

17:22.975 --> 17:24.443
♪ ♪

17:24.477 --> 17:26.479
Tube.

17:26.512 --> 17:33.486
♪ ♪

17:33.519 --> 17:34.987
Got it.

17:35.021 --> 17:37.123
[air hissing,
beeping slows]

17:37.156 --> 17:44.163
♪ ♪

17:52.004 --> 17:53.172
[dramatic musical sting]

17:53.205 --> 17:54.840
‐ Whoa.

17:54.874 --> 17:58.177
‐ Esme, there's a dozen
officers on their way.

17:58.210 --> 17:59.812
Set the gun on the stairs.

17:59.845 --> 18:02.181
‐ I'm not gonna do that.

18:02.214 --> 18:03.883
‐ Vivian, why are you
helping her?

18:03.916 --> 18:06.018
What has she got on you?
‐ Nothing.

18:06.052 --> 18:06.953
I'm just trying
to do the right thing.

18:06.986 --> 18:08.721
‐ It's your job
to enforce the laws

18:08.754 --> 18:10.156
to uphold this country.

18:10.189 --> 18:12.091
‐ What if the laws are wrong?

18:12.124 --> 18:15.094
[suspenseful music]

18:15.127 --> 18:19.365
♪ ♪

18:19.398 --> 18:20.733
Listen to me:

18:20.766 --> 18:23.869
the NFFA targeted
and killed innocent people

18:23.903 --> 18:26.238
who questioned them
last Purge Night.

18:26.272 --> 18:28.341
People like Professor Adams.

18:28.374 --> 18:30.843
Not only that,
there's proof in this building

18:30.876 --> 18:32.411
that they're killing citizens
off‐Purge.

18:32.445 --> 18:33.679
‐ That's impossible.
‐ No.

18:33.713 --> 18:36.182
I thought so, too,
but it's true.

18:36.215 --> 18:39.118
♪ ♪

18:39.151 --> 18:40.386
‐ Come on, Curtis.

18:40.419 --> 18:42.388
You haven't
pulled that trigger yet.

18:42.421 --> 18:44.023
There's a reason.

18:44.056 --> 18:47.226
You have doubts too.

18:47.259 --> 18:49.161
You have to let me do this.

18:49.195 --> 18:51.230
It's the right thing to do.

18:53.232 --> 18:55.868
We're gonna
keep walking now, okay?

18:55.901 --> 18:59.171
♪ ♪

18:59.205 --> 19:01.007
Come on.

19:01.040 --> 19:08.114
♪ ♪

19:26.966 --> 19:28.901
‐ [yelps]

19:28.934 --> 19:31.937
[dramatic music]

19:31.971 --> 19:32.805
♪ ♪

19:32.838 --> 19:34.840
[grunts]
‐ Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

19:34.874 --> 19:36.008
Vivian!

19:36.042 --> 19:37.576
Vivian, can you hear me?

19:37.610 --> 19:40.413
Huh?
Can you hear me?

19:40.446 --> 19:43.282
I'm gonna get you out of here.
‐ Please just‐‐you have to go.

19:43.315 --> 19:44.316
‐ No, no, no, no, no, no!

19:44.350 --> 19:46.285
Come on, come on.
‐ Please.

19:46.318 --> 19:49.288
[panting]

19:49.321 --> 19:50.623
♪ ♪

19:50.656 --> 19:52.591
Just tell everyone.

19:52.625 --> 19:53.826
♪ ♪

19:53.859 --> 19:57.463
‐ [panting]
Oh...

19:57.496 --> 20:00.566
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

20:00.599 --> 20:07.373
♪ ♪

20:07.406 --> 20:10.209
‐ She's stable.
You did great.

20:10.242 --> 20:13.212
‐ Thanks.
‐ Monitor her vitals.

20:13.245 --> 20:15.414
I should get out there
and help.

20:15.448 --> 20:17.550
If anything comes up,
find me.

20:17.583 --> 20:19.351
‐ Okay, I got this.
‐ Thank you, Lindsey.

20:19.385 --> 20:22.088
[indistinct chatter]

20:26.492 --> 20:28.994
[indistinct shouting]

20:29.028 --> 20:30.496
‐ Dr. Jason, how can I help?

20:30.529 --> 20:31.731
‐ More victims came in.

20:31.764 --> 20:34.066
Take her.

20:34.100 --> 20:36.035
‐ Hi, I'm Dr. Moore.

20:36.068 --> 20:39.972
♪ ♪

20:44.477 --> 20:44.844
[suspenseful music]

20:46.512 --> 20:47.947
‐ Possible explosive device.

20:47.980 --> 20:50.950
Requesting additional
surveillance on grid E‐7‐Q.

20:50.983 --> 20:53.986
Cameron 1‐1‐1‐6,
please advise.

20:56.021 --> 20:57.123
‐ [exhales sharply]

20:57.156 --> 20:58.524
‐ Tommy!

20:58.557 --> 21:00.192
♪ ♪

21:00.226 --> 21:01.994
Tommy!

21:02.027 --> 21:04.396
[indistinct chatter]

21:04.430 --> 21:06.799
[radio chatter]

21:06.832 --> 21:14.006
♪ ♪

21:15.174 --> 21:17.076
‐ [cheers]

21:17.109 --> 21:18.511
They're all loaded up
like that?

21:18.544 --> 21:20.246
[cheers]
Oh, holy shit!

21:20.279 --> 21:22.681
‐ We'll be living large
in Panama, baby.

21:22.715 --> 21:24.850
‐ Oh, yeah!
‐ Oh, bye‐bye, America.

21:24.884 --> 21:26.685
Not gonna miss you.

21:26.719 --> 21:28.387
‐ Ah, but you two are gonna
have to teach us Spanish, okay?

21:28.420 --> 21:29.989
‐ No problem.
‐ Priority alert.

21:30.022 --> 21:32.057
District two command center.

21:32.091 --> 21:33.993
10‐29 on Esme Carmona.

21:34.026 --> 21:36.162
[radio chatter]

21:36.195 --> 21:38.931
Suspect last seen
heading up south stairwell

21:38.964 --> 21:41.400
towards level four Broadcast.

21:41.433 --> 21:44.436
‐ Give me a second, baby.
Watch them.

21:44.470 --> 21:46.572
‐ Requesting special response.

21:46.605 --> 21:48.007
Termination protocol
authorized.

21:48.040 --> 21:50.409
‐ That's a hit squad.
‐ What the hell is Esme doing?

21:50.442 --> 21:51.844
‐ She's taking down
the whole fucking system.

21:51.877 --> 21:53.612
‐ What are you doing?

21:53.646 --> 21:54.880
‐ I'm gonna take it down
with her.

21:54.914 --> 21:56.615
‐ Whoa, whoa, whoa.
That's not the plan, Ryan.

21:56.649 --> 21:58.684
‐ I can't leave her.

21:58.717 --> 22:01.687
[tense music]

22:01.720 --> 22:03.088
♪ ♪

22:03.122 --> 22:04.423
‐ Then we're going too.
‐ No.

22:04.456 --> 22:06.525
‐ Back you up.
‐ No, wait, wait.

22:06.559 --> 22:09.094
You've got a family.

22:09.128 --> 22:11.297
You need to be there for them.

22:11.330 --> 22:17.269
♪ ♪

22:17.303 --> 22:20.039
I'm going alone.

22:20.072 --> 22:26.412
♪ ♪

22:26.445 --> 22:28.614
‐ We'll wait
as long as we can.

22:28.647 --> 22:31.584
♪ ♪

22:31.617 --> 22:33.152
‐ If anything happens‐‐

22:33.185 --> 22:34.286
‐ Your mom
will be taken care of.

22:34.320 --> 22:35.754
We got her no matter what.

22:35.788 --> 22:37.756
We'll see you on
the other side, man.

22:37.790 --> 22:45.030
♪ ♪

23:01.780 --> 23:05.618
[suspenseful music]

23:05.651 --> 23:06.852
‐ Let me get you a booster.

23:06.886 --> 23:09.255
Jason.

23:09.288 --> 23:13.292
Jason, where's the vaccines?

23:13.325 --> 23:15.761
Yo, hold on,
I'll be right back.

23:17.329 --> 23:19.498
Dr. Jason?

23:19.531 --> 23:26.572
♪ ♪

23:34.280 --> 23:37.182
[indistinct chatter]

23:37.216 --> 23:40.619
♪ ♪

23:40.653 --> 23:44.189
Hey, where's Dr. Jason?
‐ Haven't seen him in a while.

23:44.223 --> 23:46.325
‐ What about his cell?
‐ Didn't pick up.

23:46.358 --> 23:52.131
♪ ♪

23:52.164 --> 23:54.166
‐ Dr. Jason?

24:06.078 --> 24:09.181
Hey, guys, have you seen
Dr. Jason or Lindsey?

24:09.214 --> 24:12.318
‐ No, no one came in here
and she's doing fine.

24:12.351 --> 24:14.820
‐ Huh.
Something weird is going on.

24:14.853 --> 24:16.555
I need you guys
to stay with her.

24:16.588 --> 24:19.692
‐ Of course.
‐ Yeah, yeah.

24:27.266 --> 24:29.368
[monitor beeping rapidly]

24:29.401 --> 24:31.470
‐ Excuse me.

24:46.618 --> 24:49.421
‐ Calm down.
You're okay.

24:49.455 --> 24:51.290
Calm down, calm down.

24:51.323 --> 24:53.225
You're in a safe place.

24:53.258 --> 24:54.193
Come on.

24:54.226 --> 24:56.562
You're okay.
Take a deep breath.

24:56.595 --> 24:59.565
Ca‐‐deep breath.
Calm down.

24:59.598 --> 25:01.467
Calm down.

25:01.500 --> 25:03.135
Calm down.
You're okay.

25:12.311 --> 25:15.280
[soft unsettling music]

25:15.314 --> 25:22.354
♪ ♪

25:30.462 --> 25:33.432
[crashing, intense music]

25:33.465 --> 25:34.433
♪ ♪

25:34.466 --> 25:36.201
‐ Oh, my God.

25:36.235 --> 25:38.270
‐ [coughs]

25:38.303 --> 25:41.774
♪ ♪

25:41.807 --> 25:43.442
What happened?

25:43.475 --> 25:47.246
‐ He's killing everybody.

25:47.279 --> 25:49.581
[gasping]

25:49.615 --> 25:56.622
♪ ♪

26:11.136 --> 26:11.503
[suspenseful music]

26:13.739 --> 26:16.241
‐ Whoo!

26:16.275 --> 26:18.277
[cheering]

26:18.310 --> 26:22.381
♪ ♪

26:22.414 --> 26:24.650
‐ Yeah!
[laughs]

26:28.287 --> 26:31.523
[engines fading]

26:31.557 --> 26:38.564
♪ ♪

26:50.042 --> 26:57.049
♪ ♪

26:58.584 --> 27:01.019
‐ Keep going, move.

27:01.053 --> 27:02.588
‐ Quick!

27:02.621 --> 27:05.557
‐ Go, go, go.

27:05.591 --> 27:07.359
‐ Move up!

27:07.392 --> 27:09.194
Move!

27:09.228 --> 27:16.201
♪ ♪

27:22.141 --> 27:24.810
[alarm blaring]

27:24.843 --> 27:26.645
[gasping, panicked chatter]

27:26.678 --> 27:28.213
‐ Wait, what is this?
‐ Get down!

27:28.247 --> 27:35.354
♪ ♪

28:18.564 --> 28:21.099
‐ She's on this level.
Shoot on sight.

28:21.133 --> 28:23.735
♪ ♪

28:23.769 --> 28:25.504
‐ Hey.

28:25.537 --> 28:32.578
♪ ♪

28:33.745 --> 28:36.715
You were in the truck.

28:36.748 --> 28:39.618
We brought you here.

28:39.651 --> 28:42.654
‐ Guess you shouldn't have
done that.

28:42.688 --> 28:45.857
♪ ♪

28:45.891 --> 28:47.226
‐ Why?

28:47.259 --> 28:50.162
These‐‐these were good people.

28:50.195 --> 28:51.897
They were just trying to help.

28:51.930 --> 28:53.465
‐ Help who?

28:53.498 --> 28:55.167
♪ ♪

28:55.200 --> 28:57.869
Not Purgers.

28:57.903 --> 28:59.738
‐ What do you mean?

28:59.771 --> 29:01.506
‐ By treating
those people out there,

29:01.540 --> 29:04.810
you're robbing Purgers
of their rightful kills.

29:04.843 --> 29:05.811
‐ No, man.

29:05.844 --> 29:08.647
‐ Your patients...

29:08.680 --> 29:10.749
they're supposed to be dead.

29:10.782 --> 29:12.217
♪ ♪

29:12.251 --> 29:15.587
‐ Look...
[breathing heavily]

29:15.621 --> 29:17.222
We're just trying
to get through the night.

29:17.256 --> 29:19.524
‐ No...

29:19.558 --> 29:22.661
you're trying to play God.

29:22.694 --> 29:25.230
But you're not God.

29:25.264 --> 29:28.333
♪ ♪

29:28.367 --> 29:29.868
I am.

29:29.901 --> 29:32.871
[both grunting]

29:32.904 --> 29:35.741
[intense music]

29:35.774 --> 29:43.181
♪ ♪

29:58.797 --> 30:01.266
[both grunting]

30:01.300 --> 30:08.340
♪ ♪

30:09.474 --> 30:11.510
[high‐pitched ringing]

30:14.946 --> 30:17.883
[both grunting]

30:20.319 --> 30:25.590
♪ ♪

30:25.624 --> 30:27.592
‐ [hollers]
‐ [grunts]

30:27.626 --> 30:34.633
♪ ♪

30:41.039 --> 30:43.241
‐ [yelps]

30:43.275 --> 30:50.282
♪ ♪

30:55.454 --> 30:57.356
[gunshot]

30:57.389 --> 31:04.429
♪ ♪

31:06.031 --> 31:08.967
‐ [grunting]

31:09.000 --> 31:11.937
[suspenseful music]

31:11.970 --> 31:17.542
♪ ♪

31:17.576 --> 31:19.711
‐ Nice shot.

31:19.745 --> 31:22.547
‐ I had a good teacher.

31:22.581 --> 31:24.783
What are you doing here?
‐ I think you know.

31:24.816 --> 31:28.987
♪ ♪

31:29.020 --> 31:30.989
[panel chimes, chirps]

31:31.022 --> 31:33.558
♪ ♪

31:33.592 --> 31:36.695
‐ I have the proof.
I need to broadcast it.

31:36.728 --> 31:38.830
‐ I can buy you some time.

31:38.864 --> 31:41.533
‐ I thought you would
try and get me to run.

31:41.566 --> 31:43.869
‐ Look, I didn't come here
to save you,

31:43.902 --> 31:45.904
and I didn't come here
to talk you out of this...

31:45.937 --> 31:47.739
♪ ♪

31:47.773 --> 31:49.574
Because you're right.

31:49.608 --> 31:51.910
People need to know
the truth...

31:51.943 --> 31:54.346
and you need to tell them.

31:54.379 --> 31:59.451
♪ ♪

31:59.484 --> 32:01.820
‐ Marcus, I can't believe we're
just gonna leave him out here

32:01.853 --> 32:02.621
after what he did.

32:02.654 --> 32:03.889
‐ I'm not gonna kill him, man,

32:03.922 --> 32:07.692
but he's too dangerous
to keep inside.

32:07.726 --> 32:11.029
Let's let the Purge
take care of him.

32:16.334 --> 32:16.635
[distant gunfire]

32:19.104 --> 32:22.073
[suspenseful music]

32:22.107 --> 32:24.876
[computer chirping]
[keys tapping]

32:24.910 --> 32:26.578
‐ This glass is bulletproof,

32:26.611 --> 32:27.646
but it's not
gonna hold them forever.

32:27.679 --> 32:28.914
Not with their firepower.

32:28.947 --> 32:30.749
‐ I can push the video
to every phone in range,

32:30.782 --> 32:34.119
and I'll broadcast
as long as I can

32:34.152 --> 32:35.954
before 7:00 a. m.

32:35.987 --> 32:37.889
‐ Let me see the keycard.

32:37.923 --> 32:44.029
♪ ♪

32:44.062 --> 32:46.965
[panel chirps,
air hisses]

32:46.998 --> 32:50.368
♪ ♪

32:50.402 --> 32:52.604
‐ Wait, what‐‐?

32:52.637 --> 32:54.339
Hey.

32:54.372 --> 32:57.943
Get back inside.
They're almost here.

32:57.976 --> 33:00.912
‐ I'll stall them
until after the sirens.

33:00.946 --> 33:01.847
‐ No.

33:01.880 --> 33:03.682
‐ That way,
they can't shoot you.

33:03.715 --> 33:05.784
They'll have to arrest you.
‐ Ryan, no!

33:05.817 --> 33:08.119
Don't do this.
No, Ryan, no.

33:08.153 --> 33:09.654
Don't do this.

33:09.688 --> 33:11.423
Don't‐‐don't do this.
Please, don't.

33:11.456 --> 33:13.825
Get back in here!

33:13.859 --> 33:16.761
‐ I'm right where I need to be.

33:16.795 --> 33:17.963
‐ Don't.

33:17.996 --> 33:20.198
Ryan, listen to me.
Ryan.

33:20.232 --> 33:22.100
♪ ♪

33:22.133 --> 33:23.401
[indistinct shouting]

33:23.435 --> 33:26.438
[footsteps approaching]

33:26.471 --> 33:33.612
♪ ♪

33:38.850 --> 33:41.286
‐ Let's blow the doors.

33:41.319 --> 33:48.293
♪ ♪

33:48.326 --> 33:50.028
Clear!

33:50.061 --> 33:57.068
♪ ♪

34:06.511 --> 34:09.347
[alarm blaring]

34:09.381 --> 34:12.350
[feedback squeals]

34:12.384 --> 34:14.419
♪ ♪

34:14.452 --> 34:16.821
‐ People of New Orleans,

34:16.855 --> 34:19.391
my name is Esme Carmona.

34:19.424 --> 34:21.359
You've seen my face
and heard my name.

34:21.393 --> 34:22.761
[alarm beeping]

34:22.794 --> 34:24.729
I'm here to tell you:

34:24.763 --> 34:26.998
the Purge doesn't work.

34:27.032 --> 34:29.134
[voice echoing]
I knew a woman...

34:29.167 --> 34:31.002
a professor.

34:31.036 --> 34:33.371
She was researching
the effects of Purging...

34:33.405 --> 34:35.507
how it changes our brains.

34:35.540 --> 34:36.875
She ran a scientific study

34:36.908 --> 34:40.178
looking at regular people
like you and me.

34:40.211 --> 34:42.047
You know what she found?

34:42.080 --> 34:43.882
Proof.

34:43.915 --> 34:46.418
Proof that Purging
doesn't take away our anger,

34:46.451 --> 34:49.187
our hatred, and our fears.

34:49.220 --> 34:50.922
It fuels them.

34:50.956 --> 34:53.758
The NFFA was furious.

34:53.792 --> 34:58.096
So they decided to silence her
and destroy her evidence.

34:58.129 --> 35:02.434
Last Purge Night, the NFFA
systematically killed her

35:02.467 --> 35:05.971
along with dozens
of participants in her study.

35:06.004 --> 35:08.273
They targeted innocent people

35:08.306 --> 35:11.743
to hide
their own terrible truth,

35:11.776 --> 35:14.379
but last Purge, they couldn't
get to one woman:

35:14.412 --> 35:16.448
Olivia Hughes.

35:16.481 --> 35:19.050
So they killed her off‐Purge

35:19.084 --> 35:22.387
and they made it
look like suicide.

35:22.420 --> 35:25.256
The reason I'm being hunted

35:25.290 --> 35:28.159
is because I discovered
the truth.

35:28.193 --> 35:30.095
The video you are seeing now

35:30.128 --> 35:33.098
shows the NFFA
breaking into her house.

35:33.131 --> 35:36.768
It proves
our system is corrupt.

35:36.801 --> 35:38.069
Watch the video.

35:38.103 --> 35:39.904
Start asking questions.

35:39.938 --> 35:41.973
[sirens blaring]

35:42.007 --> 35:44.075
The truth is the only thing

35:44.109 --> 35:46.811
more powerful than this regime!

35:46.845 --> 35:49.147
[Purge alarm blaring]

35:49.180 --> 35:54.352
♪ ♪

35:54.386 --> 35:57.088
Demand the truth...

35:57.122 --> 36:01.993
♪ ♪

36:02.027 --> 36:04.396
No matter the cost.

36:04.429 --> 36:06.364
‐ [groaning]

36:06.398 --> 36:12.604
♪ ♪

36:12.637 --> 36:15.407
‐ Your lives depend on it.

36:15.440 --> 36:21.446
♪ ♪

36:21.479 --> 36:24.115
[sirens stop]

36:24.149 --> 36:27.318
[speaking Spanish]

36:27.352 --> 36:34.125
♪ ♪

36:34.159 --> 36:35.827
‐ Clear.
‐ Clear!

36:35.860 --> 36:38.496
‐ Go, go, go.
Esme Carmona, come with us.

36:46.337 --> 36:48.139
‐ Sir, we're post 7:00 a. m.

36:48.173 --> 36:50.175
‐ Orders stand.

36:50.208 --> 36:57.148
♪ ♪

37:02.020 --> 37:04.556
‐ You see?

37:04.589 --> 37:06.558
It is a lie.

37:06.591 --> 37:13.631
♪ ♪

37:38.523 --> 37:38.790
[upbeat music]

37:40.625 --> 37:42.427
‐ [singing
in foreign language]

37:42.460 --> 37:45.630
♪ ♪

37:45.663 --> 37:47.799
‐ It's a great place.
Good choice.

37:47.832 --> 37:49.467
‐ Are they?
But are they?

37:49.501 --> 37:51.803
Hey.
‐ What's going on?

37:51.836 --> 37:54.539
‐ You're late.
‐ Old habits.

37:54.572 --> 37:57.542
‐ Keep the change.
‐ Gracias.

37:57.575 --> 37:59.477
‐ [laughs]

37:59.511 --> 38:02.380
